[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Ad [Addendum] 27. Witt Library. St. John preaching in the Wilderness. Sermon of St. John; 1) Düsseldorf 43 x 63 cm old engraving [onleesbaar] from [onleesbaar] Brueghel le Vieux, N° 329; 2) Vienna, Baronin Oppenheim [...] as P.B.d.Ä. varia N° 34 rather good version but hardly original; 3) Dresden N° 819a [...] the portrait omitted, delicate painting Jan B. esp. Head on right, cf. Bailleur; [blad 1, verso] 4) E. Parsons, London Advertisment Burl. Mag. Dec. 1928, panel 40 1/2 x 66 cm rather poor; 5) Berandière Sale, Am. Art Assoc. N.York 11-12 Dec. 1930, cradled panel, 305, signed at lower left at foot of tree: P. BRVEGEL 45 x 64 cm differing in protportions from original; 6) Public Library Arbroath [...] with figures added from Conversion of Paul (2 men on horseback) portrait omitted; [blad 2, recto] Johannespredigt continued 7) Batthiany, from Ztschft f.b.Kst. [Zeitschrift für bildende Kunst] 1913 [=1914], XLIX, p. 38 - the original.
